description: Installation of an air source heat pump and solar thermal panels
decision_conditions: The development to which this permission relates shall be begun not later than the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.

Reason: To comply with Section 91 of the Town & Country Planning Act 1990. | The development hereby approved shall be in accordance with drawings and documents:  Proposed Fence Details 1025-GP-PL-07, Existing and Proposed Elevational Images 1025-GP-PL-06, Proposed Site Plan 1025-GP-PL-05, Existing Site Plan 1025-GP-PL-04, Block Plan 1025-GP-PL-02, Location Plan 1025-GP-PL-01, Environmental Noise Survey and Plant Noise Assessment Report Issue 4 by Noico (March 2023), Specification of Ecodan Air Source Heat Pump, Specification of Solar Panels.

Reason: For the avoidance of doubt, and in the interests of proper planning. | The recommendations for noise mitigation measures set out in the submitted Environmental Noise Survey and Plant Noise Assessment Report Issue 4 by Noico (March 2023), shall be fully implemented prior to first operation of the development hereby approved.

Reason: To safeguard adjoining occupiers of the development against unacceptable noise, disturbance and emissions, policies 1.1(j) of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy (2012), Local Variation policy 3.5 and policy 7A of Ealing's Development Management DPD (2013) and policies D14 and SI1 of the London Plan (2021); and National Planning Policy Framework (2021).
